tergites V-VI 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20</emphasis>
pelta; 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. brunneicornus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="brunneicornus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. brunneicornus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">21</emphasis>
): 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">21</emphasis>
pelta. Scale bars: 100 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head 1.6 times as long as wide (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 14–21" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 14 - 21. Apterygothrips spp. A. flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. (14 - 20) 14 adult, female 15 adult, male 16 head, pronotum and fore legs 17 tergites IX-X, female 18 tergites IX-X, male 19 tergites V-VI 20 pelta; A. brunneicornus (21): 21 pelta. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures14-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713605" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface almost smooth; ocelli absent; eyes not prolonged ventrally, postocular setae well developed but shorter than eyes, pointed at apex (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 14–21" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 14 - 21. Apterygothrips spp. A. flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. (14 - 20) 14 adult, female 15 adult, male 16 head, pronotum and fore legs 17 tergites IX-X, female 18 tergites IX-X, male 19 tergites V-VI 20 pelta; A. brunneicornus (21): 21 pelta. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures14-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713605" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16</figureCitation>
); cheeks weakly rounded. Mouth-cone rounded, maxillary stylets retracted into postocular setae, about half of head width apart at middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 14–21" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 14 - 21. Apterygothrips spp. A. flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. (14 - 20) 14 adult, female 15 adult, male 16 head, pronotum and fore legs 17 tergites IX-X, female 18 tergites IX-X, male 19 tergites V-VI 20 pelta; A. brunneicornus (21): 21 pelta. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures14-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713605" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16</figureCitation>
). Antenna 8-segmented, sensoria small, III with 0+1, VI with 1+1, V with 1+1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum almost smooth, notopleural sutures complete (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
); am and ml minute, other three pairs of major setae well developed, pointed at apex, epim the longest (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
); mesopresternum reduced to two small, lateral triangular plates, completely eroded medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9</figureCitation>
); metanotum smooth, metathoracic sternopleural sutures absent. All legs normal, without fore tarsal tooth (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 14–21" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 14 - 21. Apterygothrips spp. A. flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. (14 - 20) 14 adult, female 15 adult, male 16 head, pronotum and fore legs 17 tergites IX-X, female 18 tergites IX-X, male 19 tergites V-VI 20 pelta; A. brunneicornus (21): 21 pelta. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures14-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713605" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Abdomen</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pelta smooth and hemicircular, with a pair of campaniform sensilla (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 14–21" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 14 - 21. Apterygothrips spp. A. flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. (14 - 20) 14 adult, female 15 adult, male 16 head, pronotum and fore legs 17 tergites IX-X, female 18 tergites IX-X, male 19 tergites V-VI 20 pelta; A. brunneicornus (21): 21 pelta. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures14-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713605" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites II-VII without wing-retaining setae (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 14–21" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 14 - 21. Apterygothrips spp. A. flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. (14 - 20) 14 adult, female 15 adult, male 16 head, pronotum and fore legs 17 tergites IX-X, female 18 tergites IX-X, male 19 tergites V-VI 20 pelta; A. brunneicornus (21): 21 pelta. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures14-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713605" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">19</figureCitation>
); tergite IX setae developed, but all shorter than tube, pointed at apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">12</figureCitation>
); tube about 0.5 times as long as head, 1.6 times as long as basal width, anal setae slightly shorter than tube (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 14–21" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 14 - 21. Apterygothrips spp. A. flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. (14 - 20) 14 adult, female 15 adult, male 16 head, pronotum and fore legs 17 tergites IX-X, female 18 tergites IX-X, male 19 tergites V-VI 20 pelta; A. brunneicornus (21): 21 pelta. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures14-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713605" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Measurements</emphasis>
(holotype female in microns). Body length 1580. Head length 175, width across eyes 110; eye length 50, postocular setae length 35. Antenna length 265, segments I-VIII length (width) 25(30), 35(25), 35(20), 35(25), 35(20), 30(20), 25(20) and 20(10), sensoria on segment III length 10. Pronotum length 130, width 155, length of pronotal setae: am 5, aa 15, ml 5, epim 30, pa 25. Pelta length 65, width 125; tergite IX posteromarginal setae S1-S3, 65, 80, 75; tube length 80, basal width 50, apical width 30; anal setae length 75.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male aptera</emphasis>
. Very similar to female (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 14–21" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 14 - 21. Apterygothrips spp. A. flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. (14 - 20) 14 adult, female 15 adult, male 16 head, pronotum and fore legs 17 tergites IX-X, female 18 tergites IX-X, male 19 tergites V-VI 20 pelta; A. brunneicornus (21): 21 pelta. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures14-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713605" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">15</figureCitation>
), fore legs without fore tarsal tooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergite IX setae S2 short and stout (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–13" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 13. Apterygothrips flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. 6 head, pronotum and fore leg, female 7 head, pronotum and fore leg, male 8 antenna 9 mesopresternum 10 pelta 11 abdominal tergite V 12 abdominal tergites IX-X, female 13 abdominal tergites IX-X, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures6-13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713604" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 14–21" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 14 - 21. Apterygothrips spp. A. flavescens Dang &amp; Qiao sp. nov. (14 - 20) 14 adult, female 15 adult, male 16 head, pronotum and fore legs 17 tergites IX-X, female 18 tergites IX-X, male 19 tergites V-VI 20 pelta; A. brunneicornus (21): 21 pelta. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1112.85902.figures14-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713605" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18</figureCitation>
), sternites without a pore plate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Measurements</emphasis>
(paratype male in microns). Body length 1225. Head length 160, width across eyes 105; eye length 50, postocular setae length 30. Antenna length 250, segments I-VIII length (width): 25(25), 35(20), 30(20), 30(20), 30(20), 30(20), 25(20) and 20(10), sensoria on segment III length 10. Pronotum length 100, width 125, length of pronotal setae: am 5, aa 15, ml 5, epim 20, pa 10. Pelta length 45, width 95; tergite IX posteromarginal setae S1-S3, 70, 20, 85; tube length 75, basal width 50, apical width 25; anal setae length 75.
</paragraph>
